<ns-panel id="first-time" decoration="">
  <ns-lockup>
    <h2 slot="heading">
      <span class="h5">Topping up for the first time.</span>
      <span class="h2 enlighten">How to <b>top up for the first time</b></span>
    </h2>
      <div slot="paragraph">
        <p>You'll need to activate your key or card in your meter first.</p>
        <ul class="ul-bullet">
          <li>Put your key or card into the meter for at least a minute to activate it</li>
          <li>Take your key or card to a <a href="#payzone">Payzone</a> or <a href="#post-office">Post Office</a> to top up</li>
          <li>Put the key or card into your meter (electricity credit will transfer automatically)</li>
          <li>For gas, press and hold the red button 'A' to transfer the credit to the meter.</li>     
        </ul>
      </div>      
    <div slot="image">
      <ns-image src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52657167/84566809-0c244c00-ad6c-11ea-90ee-02e215429b21.jpg"></ns-image>
    </div>
  </ns-lockup>
</ns-panel>

<ns-panel>
  <div class="splash triple">

    <ns-card id="post-office" type="support">
      <h3 slot="heading">Top-up at the Post Office</h3>
      <p slot="paragraph">You’ll need the smart card that is linked to your meter to top up like this. A mininmum top up of £1 is required, and you'll always need to top up to the nearest pound.</p>
      <p slot="paragraph">So you can't add £8.50, but you could add £8 or £9.</p>
      <div slot="cta">
        <ns-cta type="text" href="#">Find your nearest Post Office</ns-cta>
      </div>
    </ns-card>

    <ns-card id="payzone" type="support">
      <h3 slot="heading">Top up at a Payzone</h3>
      <p slot="paragraph">You can top up anywhere with the Payzone symbol using your card or key.</p>
      <p slot="paragraph">You'll need to top up at least £1 each time – and to the nearest whole pound. So you can't add £8.50, but you could do £8 or £9.</p>
      <div slot="cta">
        <ns-cta type="text" href="#">Find your nearest Payzone</ns-cta>
      </div>
    </ns-card>

  </div>
</ns-panel>


<ns-panel id="faq">
