    <h3 slot="heading">Frequently asked questions</h3> 
    
    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">I'm leaving British Gas. What happens next?</h4>

      <p>We're sorry to see you go. Here's what will happen.</p>

      <p>1. We'll close your account on a date of your choice.</p>

      <p>2. Your new supplier should ask you for your final meter reading, which they'll send to us.</p>

      <p>3. We'll then give you a final bill based on this meter reading. But if we don't get one, we'll estimate it.</p>

      <p>4. If we owe you money, we'll send it to you via cheque.</p>

    </ns-expander>

    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">What should I do if my gas card isn't working?</h4>
      <p>Your meter or card could be broken - wipe the gold chip on the card and try again. Check your meter for error messages too. If there is one, check <a href="#">Understanding messages on your meter</a>.</p>

      <p>If there's no error message on your meter and your card isn't working at your local <a href="#">Payzone</a> then you need a new card. Just ask the shopkeeper and they should give you one for free.</p>

      <p>If you think your meter's broken, <a href="#">start a Live Chat</a> with one of our advisers to get a new one. You'll need your meter's serial number handy – it should be next to the barcode under the screen. But don't worry if you can't find it, we'll help you when you chat to us. You'll need to be near your meter and please make a note of any error messages on the screen.</p>
    </ns-expander>

    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">What should I do if my electricity key isn't working?</h4>
      <p>Your meter or or key could be broken. Blow any dust off the gold contacts on the key and try again. Check your meter for error messages too. And if there is one, check our guide to <a href="#">understanding messages on your meter</a>.</p>

      <p>If there isn't an error message on your meter and your key isn't working at your local Payzone, then you'll need a new key.</p>

      <p>We can get it sorted over <a href="#">Live Chat</a> – you'll just need your meter's serial number which begins with S or F (it's usually next to the barcode under the screen). We'll give you a reference number and ask you to wait at least half an hour. Then you'll be able to collect your new key from your local <a href="#">Payzone</a>.</p>

    </ns-expander>

    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">Can I get my lost credit back?</h4>
      <p>Yes, we can give you back any money left on your key or card when you lost it. You might have to give us proof of buying the credit before we refund you though.</p>

      <p>How to get a credit refund.</p>

      <ul class="ul-bullet">
        <li>Ask us for a refund using <a href="#">Live Chat</a> (you can order a new key or card at the same time)</li>
        <li>Tell us how much was on your lost card or key - We'll check our system to see if it's right </li>
        <li>If it is, we'll transfer the credit onto your new card or key.</li>   
      </ul>

    </ns-expander>

    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">My new house has a prepayment meter installed. What should I do?</h4>
      <p>If you've just moved house and your new home already has a Pay As You Go meter, call our <a href="#">24-hour automated line</a> to find out what to do next.</p>
    </ns-expander>

    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">Can I switch from a prepayment meter to a regular (credit) meter?</h4>
      <p>If you want to switch to a regular meter, just call our <a href="#">24-hour automated line</a> to get it sorted.</p>
    </ns-expander>

    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">What do I do if the credit from my old meter isn’t showing?</h4>
      <p>Once you've had a new meter installed, it can take up to 24 hours for any credit left on your old meter to transfer over.</p>
    </ns-expander>

    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">How does emergency credit work?</h4>
      <p>We never want to leave you without any gas and electricity – even when you can't top up. So every British Gas meter has £5 of Emergency Credit for when you've run out of credit but you're unable to top up.</p>
      <p>To find out how it works, go to our <a href="https://www.britishgas.co.uk/help-and-support/meters/using-emergency-credit"> Emergency Credit page</a>.</p>
    </ns-expander>

    <ns-expander role="tab">
      <h4 slot="heading">How can I control how much I spend?</h4>
      <p>Your Pay As You Go meter gives you ultimate control over how much you're spending on your energy – making it easier to stay in budget.</p>
      <p>By paying for your energy before you use it, you won't be faced with unexpected bills or late payment fees. Just the energy you need, when you need it.</p>
    </ns-expander>
